Abstract: This paper examines the extent of foreign currency and/or parent company currency financial measures used by 105 U.K.-based MNCs in the process of evaluting foreign subsidiary operations and their managers&apos; performance.The results of the empirical study indicate a preference towards the use of local currency measures and the extent of this preference tends to be greater than those found in recent similar studies of U.s.-based MNCs.&copy; 1988 JIBS. Journal of International Business Studies (1988) 19, 257&ndash;275
